Consumer: python hw7_consumer.py

The producer sends messages to the green-trips topic.
Redpanda (the Kafka broker) writes those messages to disk on the redpanda-1 container.
The green-trips topic’s partitions are those log files on disk.
So the data is stored in the green-trips topic itself. There is no separate database or table; the topic partitions are the storage.
  
